            <div class="comment-body"><p>A phone doesn't queue, can't handle you being in the loo, and so on.  And for dealing with live people, it's usually "the program left a crash dump here and there, just mail it to me" -- ie, the mail is <b>in addition</b> to the phone call.  And at that point, the live human already knows you are aware, so you're adding an hour to your response time for no gain (greylisting's 90% rejected spam doesn't add up with most other techniques).</p></div>
