<article class="comment-article com-show" id="tree_43447935" data-cid="43447935">
    <div id="comment_43447935">
        <header data-points="2" data-reason="Normal">
            <h3 class="comment-title" data-subject="Re:Greylist instead"><i class="com-toggle fa fa-caret-down"></i>Re:Greylist instead<span> (2)</span></h3>
            <h4 class="avatar-tiny"><a href="//beta.slashdot.org/~dskoll" class="author" title="author name and user ID">dskoll (99328) </a> | about a year ago | <a href="//beta.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=3647643&cid=43447935">(#43447935)</a></h4>
        </header>
        <div id="comment_body_43447935" class="comment-wrapper" data-points="2" data-reason="Normal">
            <div class="comment-body"><p> <i>and all mails you get will be delayed by an hour or more</i>

</p><p>Only if you have a broken and/or stupid greylist implementation.  A correct implementation will refrain (for a few weeks) from greylisting an IP address once it notices that it does retry.  That makes the initial delays quite tolerable.</p></div>
