        <article class="comment-article com-show" id="tree_43451317" data-cid="43451317">
    <div id="comment_43451317">
        <header data-points="1" data-reason="Normal">
            <h3 class="comment-title" data-subject="Re:Greylist instead"><i class="com-toggle fa fa-caret-down"></i>Re:Greylist instead<span> (1)</span></h3>
            <h4 class="avatar-tiny"><a href="//beta.slashdot.org/~dskoll" class="author" title="author name and user ID">dskoll (99328) </a> | about a year ago | <a href="//beta.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=3647643&cid=43451317">(#43451317)</a></h4>
        </header>
        <div id="comment_body_43451317" class="comment-wrapper" data-points="1" data-reason="Normal">
            <div class="comment-body"><p>I'm not sure what you mean by "breakage notifications"

</p><p>If you're referring to automated alerts and the like, obviously you don't greylist those because you know (or should know) either the originating IP address, the envelope sender, or both.</p></div>
