            <h4 class="avatar-tiny"><span class="author" title="author name and user ID">Anonymous Coward</span> | about a year ago | <a href="//beta.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=3647643&cid=43451133">(#43451133)</a></h4>
        </header>
        <div id="comment_body_43451133" class="comment-wrapper" data-points="0" data-reason="Normal">
            <div class="comment-body"><p><div class="quote"><p>Use greylisting as a first defense - easily configurable in postfix, and it reduces the amount of spam dramatically.   This relies on the behavior of the sender, rather than someone else's opinion of them.</p></div><p>Greylisting use to be HIGHLY effective against botnet spammers, the majority. However, as always, the spammers saw the defense mechanism and upped their game. Greylisting is now largely ineffective against spam. Most spammers now retry delivery and Spamassassin is again grinding under the load.</p><p>What now?</p></div>
