            <h3 class="comment-title" data-subject="SpamAssassin just called..."><i class="com-toggle fa fa-caret-down"></i>SpamAssassin just called...<span> (1)</span></h3>
            <h4 class="avatar-tiny"><a href="//beta.slashdot.org/~John+Bokma" class="author" title="author name and user ID">John Bokma (834313) </a> | about a year ago | <a href="//beta.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=3647643&cid=43448215">(#43448215)</a></h4>
        </header>
        <div id="comment_body_43448215" class="comment-wrapper" data-points="1" data-reason="Normal">
            <div class="comment-body">What you describe is SpamAssassin. The scores are learned by feeding a lot of ham and spam and finding the right balance. Of course you can (re)train the scoring with your own ham &amp; spam, and add your own rules, etc.</div>
