<article class="comment-article com-show" id="tree_43447661" data-cid="43447661">
    <div id="comment_43447661">
        <header data-points="-1" data-reason="Normal">
            <h3 class="comment-title" data-subject="Should only Blacklist "worst of the worst""><i class="com-toggle fa fa-caret-down"></i>Should only Blacklist "worst of the worst"<span> (-1)</span></h3>
            <h4 class="avatar-tiny"><span class="author" title="author name and user ID">Anonymous Coward</span> | about a year ago | <a href="//beta.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=3647643&cid=43447661">(#43447661)</a></h4>
        </header>
        <div id="comment_body_43447661" class="comment-wrapper" data-points="-1" data-reason="Normal">
            <div class="comment-body"><p>A successful 'blacklist' is a very dangerous thing indeed, and will soon attract the attention of villains every bit as wicked as those placed on the list. The only way to prevent a 'blacklist' from being abused is to ensure the 'cut-off' position is set as high as possible. For spammers, this means only the worst offenders should be included to avoid the "burn the witch" phenomenon.</p><p>When a blacklist acts more like a vigilante "judge, jury and executioner" mechanism against disliked behaviour, it will do far more harm than good. Big, persistent spammers (including ordinary companies that attempt to exploit this method of 'promotion') should be on the list for sure. In the case of corporate entities that offend, and whose main business model is NOT spam, they should be rapidly removed from such list IF/WHEN they reform their behaviour.</p><p>Small time spammers, and small acts of abusing spamming should NEVER end up on the blacklist. This isn't the job or role of any trustworthy list. The list should only be seen as a final, desperate level of protection, not an act of 'law enforcement'.</p><p>By only fighting the mighty, evil spammers the list will maintain maximum support, and will also improve the legal landscape when these mighty spammers fight and lose in court. The purpose of such a list should actually be to encourage the 'enemy' to attempt a legal battle. On the other hand, a despicable, cowardly blacklist will take pride in mostly including those without the resources for fighting back.</p></div>
            <footer class="comment-footer" id="comment_footer_43447661">
                <div class="comment-footer-controls btn-group btn-group-sm" data-sid="3647643" data-cid="43447661">
                    <button class="btn btn-default call-form" data-sid="43447661" data-pid="43447661" data-cid="43447661"><i class="fa fa-reply"></i> Reply</button>
                    <button class="btn btn-default show-parent" href=""><i class="fa fa-level-up"></i> Parent</button>
